## 3.4 Worked Example 4 — Form Validation using Superglobals

```php
<?php
    // form.html posts to process.php
    // process.php

    if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {
        $name  = trim($_POST["name"]   ?? "");
        $email = trim($_POST["email"]  ?? "");
        $age   = (int)($_POST["age"]   ?? 0);
        $errors = [];

        // Validation rules
        if (empty($name))              $errors[] = "Name required";
        if (!filter_var($email, FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL))
                                        $errors[] = "Invalid email";
        if ($age < 17 || $age > 100)   $errors[] = "Age must be 17-100";

        if (empty($errors)) {
            echo "✅ Welcome, $name! Registration successful.";
        } else {
            echo "❌ Errors:<ul>";
            foreach ($errors as $e) echo "<li>$e</li>";
            echo "</ul>";
        }
    }
?>
```

### Analytical Matrix — Superglobals Comparison

| Superglobal | Source | Visibility | Typical Use |
|---|---|---|---|
| `$_GET` | URL query string | Visible in URL | Search filters |
| `$_POST` | HTTP request body | Hidden | Login forms |
| `$_REQUEST` | Both GET + POST + COOKIE | Mixed | Avoid in production |
| `$_COOKIE` | Client-side file | User-modifiable | Remember-me |
| `$_SESSION` | Server-side file | Hidden | Auth state |
| `$_SERVER` | Server metadata | Read-only | IP, headers, paths |
| `$_FILES` | Uploaded files | Form-encoded | File upload |
| `$_ENV` | Environment vars | Server-config | DB credentials |
| `$GLOBALS` | All global scope | Reference | Rarely used |
