### Question 1: Define Server-Side Scripting. List any two advantages of server-side scripting over client-side scripting.

> **[KTU University Exam – May 2024, Model Paper 2]**

**Model Answer (≈3 marks):**

**Definition (1 mark):**
Server-side scripting is a web development technique in which scripts run on the web server (not the client's browser) to generate dynamic content that is then sent to the client as plain HTML.

**Two Advantages (2 marks — 1 each):**
1. **Security** — Source code, database credentials, and business logic are never exposed to the client. Sensitive operations (login, payment, DB writes) can be safely performed.
2. **Database Access** — Server-side languages (PHP, Python, Java) have native drivers for MySQL/PostgreSQL/MongoDB, allowing persistent storage that is impossible from the browser.
3. *Optional extras:* Cross-browser consistency, no dependency on client's hardware/OS, central updates.

