### Question 2: Differentiate between `abstract class` and `interface` in PHP with an example.

> **[KTU University Exam – Dec 2023]**

**Model Answer (≈3 marks):**

| Feature | Abstract Class | Interface |
|---|---|---|
| **Keyword** | `abstract class` | `interface` |
| **Methods** | Can have abstract AND concrete | All methods abstract (pre-PHP 8) |
| **Variables** | Can have `$properties` | Cannot have properties (only `const`) |
| **Inheritance** | `extends` (one only) | `implements` (multiple allowed) |
| **Access modifiers** | `public`, `protected`, `private` | All methods must be `public` |
| **When to use** | "Is-a" relationship + shared code | Pure contract / "can-do" capability |

**Example (1 mark):**
```php
<?php
    interface Drawable {           // pure contract
        public function draw();
    }
    abstract class Shape {          // partial implementation
        protected $color;
        abstract public function area();
        public function setColor($c) { $this->color = $c; }
    }
?>
```

