> [!WARNING]
> **🚨 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning — Where Students Lose Marks:**
> 1. **Forgetting `$` prefix on variables** — `$name` vs `name` is a syntax error.
> 2. **Case-sensitivity confusion** — variables ARE case-sensitive; functions/classes are NOT.
> 3. **Missing `break;` in `switch`** — causes fall-through and is a common 2-mark deduction.
> 4. **Using `==` instead of `===`** — loose comparison gives unexpected results (e.g., `"0" == false` is true).
> 5. **Forgetting `public/private/protected`** on class members — in PHP 8+ properties **must** declare a visibility.
> 6. **Not calling `parent::__construct()`** in child class — parent properties won't initialize.
> 7. **Mixing single and double quotes** — `"$var"` interpolates; `'$var'` does not. This single mistake loses 1-2 marks.
> 8. **Outputting raw `$_GET`/`$_POST` to HTML** — security hole (XSS). Use `htmlspecialchars()`.
> 9. **Using `rsort` instead of `arsort`** for associative arrays — loses the keys, which the question usually requires.
> 10. **Defining multiple `<?php` blocks redundantly** — not an error, but indicates poor code structure to examiners.

