## 🔁 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Rapid-Revision Checklist)

### A. Server-Side vs Client-Side
- ✅ Server-side runs on the **web server**; client-side runs in the **browser**.
- ✅ Server-side is **secure**; client-side exposes source.
- ✅ PHP, Python (Django/Flask), Java (Spring), Node.js, Ruby on Rails are server-side.

### B. PHP Basics
- ✅ PHP file extension: **`.php`**.
- ✅ Code must be inside `<?php ... ?>` tags.
- ✅ Variables start with `$` and are **case-sensitive**.
- ✅ Strings: single quotes = literal, double quotes = **interpolate** variables.
- ✅ Concatenation: `.` (period), not `+`.
- ✅ Echo is faster than print and has no return value.
- ✅ Comments: `//`, `#`, `/* */`.

### C. Program Control
- ✅ `if/elseif/else` — multi-branch conditional.
- ✅ `switch` — multi-way with `break;` to prevent fall-through.
- ✅ Loops: `while`, `do-while`, `for`, **`foreach`** (for arrays).
- ✅ `break` exits loop; `continue` skips to next iteration.
- ✅ Ternary `$x = (cond) ? a : b;` and null-coalescing `??`.

### D. Functions
- ✅ Defined with `function name(args) { return value; }`.
- ✅ Default parameter values allowed.
- ✅ **Scoping:** local, global (use `global` keyword), **static** (preserves state).
- ✅ `...$args` for variadic functions (PHP 5.6+).
- ✅ Anonymous functions via `$var = function() { ... };`.
- ✅ Arrow functions: `fn($x) => $x * 2` (PHP 7.4+).

### E. Arrays
- ✅ PHP arrays are **ordered maps** (key-value pairs).
- ✅ Three types: **Indexed, Associative, Multidimensional**.
- ✅ Indexed: integer keys auto-assigned from 0.
- ✅ Associative: string keys defined by user.
- ✅ Multidimensional: array of arrays.
- ✅ `count()`, `sort`/`rsort` (numeric), `asort`/`arsort` (preserve keys), `ksort` (by key).
- ✅ `array_push`/`array_pop` for stack ops; `array_shift`/`array_unshift` for queue ops.
- ✅ `in_array` to test existence; `array_search` to find key.
- ✅ `array_map`, `array_filter`, `array_reduce` for functional style.

### F. Classes and Objects
- ✅ Class = blueprint; Object = instance.
- ✅ Created with `new ClassName()`.
- ✅ Access from inside: `$this->property`.
- ✅ Access from outside: `$obj->property` (if public).
- ✅ **Constructor:** `__construct()`, **Destructor:** `__destruct()`.
- ✅ **Constants:** `const NAME = value;` accessed via `ClassName::NAME`.
- ✅ Access modifiers: `public` (anywhere), `protected` (class + subclass), `private` (class only).
- ✅ **Inheritance:** `class Child extends Parent` — single only.
- ✅ **Polymorphism:** method overriding in subclass with same signature.
- ✅ **Abstract classes:** `abstract class C { abstract function f(); }` — cannot instantiate.
- ✅ **Interfaces:** `interface I { public function f(); }` — all methods abstract pre-PHP 8; multiple implements allowed.
- ✅ **Static members:** `static $var;` accessed via `ClassName::$var` or `self::$var`.
- ✅ **`instanceof`** — type-checking operator.
- ✅ **4 Pillars of OOP:** Encapsulation, Abstraction, Inheritance, Polymorphism.

### G. Exam Strategy — Top 5 KTU Traps
- 🎯 Use `===` (strict comparison) over `==` in PHP.
- 🎯 Use `htmlspecialchars()` for any user input echoed to HTML.
- 🎯 Always include `break;` in every `switch` case.
- 🎯 `arsort` (not `rsort`) for descending sort of associative arrays.
- 🎯 `parent::__construct()` must be explicitly called in child classes.
