## 5.3 TOPIC RECAP & IMPORTANT THINGS TO REMEMBER

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Rapid Revision Checklist — Must-Know for KTU 2024 Exam:**

- **Three-tier architecture:** Client (browser) → Application (PHP server) → Data (MySQL). **Client NEVER connects directly to database.**
- **LAMP/LEMP Stack:** Linux + Apache/Nginx + MySQL + PHP — powers ~40% of all websites.
- **SQL Sub-languages:** DDL (schema), DML (data), DCL (permissions), TCL (transactions).
- **CRUD Mapping:** Create=INSERT, Read=SELECT, Update=UPDATE, Delete=DELETE.
- **WHERE vs HAVING:** WHERE filters rows before grouping (no aggregates); HAVING filters groups after (aggregates allowed).
- **JOIN Types:** INNER (matches only), LEFT (all left + matched right), RIGHT, FULL OUTER, CROSS, SELF.
- **Aggregates:** `COUNT()`, `SUM()`, `AVG()`, `MIN()`, `MAX()` — used with `GROUP BY`.
- **Deprecated:** `mysql_*` functions (gone since PHP 7). Use **`mysqli_*` or `PDO`**.
- **`mysqli` vs `PDO`:** `mysqli` = MySQL-only, supports both procedural and OOP. `PDO` = 12+ drivers, OOP only, exception-based.
- **Connection Functions:** `mysqli_connect(host, user, pass, dbname)` returns `FALSE` on failure; `new PDO(dsn, user, pass)` throws `PDOException`.
- **Charset:** Always set to **`utf8mb4`** to support full Unicode (Indian names, emojis).
- **Prepared Statements:** Use `?` or `:name` placeholders. `prepare()` → `bind_param()`/`execute()` → `fetch()`. **Mandatory** for security.
- **SQL Injection:** Always exploit non-parameterized queries. Use prepared statements + `password_hash()` + `password_verify()` (bcrypt).
- **Fetch Functions:** `mysqli_fetch_assoc()` (1 row, assoc array), `mysqli_fetch_all()` (all rows), `mysqli_num_rows()` (count).
- **PDO Fetch Modes:** `PDO::FETCH_ASSOC` (assoc array), `PDO::FETCH_OBJ` (object), `PDO::FETCH_BOTH` (both keys).
- **Transaction Lifecycle:** `START TRANSACTION` → SQL ops → `COMMIT` (success) or `ROLLBACK` (failure).
- **PHP Data Types for Binding:** `i` (int), `s` (string), `d` (double), `b` (blob).
- **Closing Order:** Free result set first (`mysqli_free_result`), then close connection (`mysqli_close`). For PDO, unset the object.

> **Best of luck with your KTU 2024 End Semester Examination! Keep the 3-tier model, CRUD mapping, and prepared statements as your three pillars.**

